  "summary": "Hester Aggles calls Dr. Donald Craig to cancel their scheduled lecture, explaining that her family has received complicated news. She reveals that they have discovered her brother, Jack, did not kill their mother, but she insists that he keep this information secret and requests that he does not visit. While Leo Aggles views the exoneration of Jack as happy news, Hester finds the revelation distressing and believes it will only cause further annoyance.\n\nGwendolyn Vance calls Mick, who reacts to the news of the missing witness by suggesting they meet with Andrew Marshall to seek advice. Mick jokingly wonders if one of them is the culprit, a comment that Leo finds potentially serious.\n\nIn a separate location, Mary Darland attends to her husband, Philip, who suffers from muscle atrophy due to polio. Philip discusses the news regarding Jack's exoneration, noting that the Marshall Law Firm is practical and will likely accept the findings. Mary expresses discomfort with the social scrutiny and the \"dreadful\" nature of the situation, though she notes that since the perpetrator is dead, the matter is over. Philip observes that Mary's discreet handling of the situation has been perfect. As Mary tends to Philip's physical discomfort, the phone rings; she answers and informs Philip that the caller is Mick.",
